PFM Logistics is a leading national sensitive freight and logistics company,
specialising in delivery, storage, and installations.

Our Clients vary across multiple industries including Print, Medical,
Refrigeration & ATMs.

Our business is rapidly growing and we are looking for an all-round Transport
and Warehousing system support resource. The role requires strong technical
analysis and problem-solving skills and operates autonomously to implement
proactive customer technical solutions.

** Duties and Responsibilities: **

  * Prioritising incoming support requests via phone call and email from internal staff and external customers to swiftly troubleshoot issues. 
  * Resolving Level 1 and 2 support tickets and escalating where required. 
  * Logging and managing tickets with precision, ensuring nothing slips through the cracks. 
  * Escalating and managing tasks to MSP and other external vendors, to ensure required services are delivered nationally. 
  * Configuration, monitoring and fixing of EDI files, including reviewing, and modifying XML, CSV and JSON files. 
  * Data entry and record maintenance in our internal TMS and WMS applications. 
  * Carry out and report on testing of TMS and WMS system updates and new features. 
  * Documenting support activities, including solutions, procedures, and processes. 
  * Mobile app support, installing and updating on Phones and Warehouse Scanners and linking with Cloud applications. 

